A "400 Bad Request" error with SambaNova indicates that the server couldn't process your request due to invalid syntax or input values [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFXiBJFyAK8csIanbE9Jcm6DxJgaAX183f_OrHenr310pAPpCo75Y8SDit_vC1C7C04B8Yc2jn9FC2TP2WXXJpNg0rTKUwX4aJdtfFjeFzBP_5DWqipBJNMDqlUAaHBPHx9p3unslCJG9m1kU-6IM-bSFp3IjD4oniP9hXK7Id_cykgnrop6g==). This generally means the client (your application or browser) sent a request that the server couldn't understand [quora](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG6Lt6fxkcfIJiOzi0SNEmfLpp5eyE9oH2JvH6NkMN77usUKPOwcua41eXWwePsH-Dy4YuE_aERV4L0pMTlhc6zghjNjqjdVx89H2Ukd3Lwvqh4aygCOrz1DxzFM8sPfUoWoBdd6QLBDJ5cNfYL9j4Wx19Ns9LYvrDoCBQS7Tl_yoblNyMR3Os=]. When a request fails, the SambaNova Cloud API responds with a JSON object containing details about the error, including an error code, the parameter causing the error (if applicable), and a helpful error message [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF_UAZaQtEPrpRGgBY-ecbeKE6BJm7FOy0h06E3nR_aAgBmR-on70aM4YANoktNIp1p7h4c15xM9VuFqpxE4aRVirxdJCyiN9WOh0y-f-X5mYKS6f2VrdPdbzN_2RSWnE0yLOIoe7P2-oLf1FrbKddy8Mnb1KadDE88qa56) [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFXiBJFyAK8csIanbE9Jcm6DxJgaAX183f_OrHenr310pAPpCo75Y8SDit_vC1C7C04B8Yc2jn9FC2TP2WXXJpNg0rTKUwX4aJdtfFjeFzBP_5DWqipBJNMDqlUAaHBPHx9p3unslCJG9m1kU-6IM-bSFp3IjD4oniP9hXK7Id_cykgnrop6g==].

Here's how to troubleshoot:

1.  **Invalid Syntax or Input Values:** Double-check your API request syntax and parameters [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFXiBJFyAK8csIanbE9Jcm6DxJgaAX183f_OrHenr310pAPpCo75Y8SDit_vC1C7C04B8Yc2jn9FC2TP2WXXJpNg0rTKUwX4aJdtfFjeFzBP_5DWqipBJNMDqlUAaHBPHx9p3unslCJG9m1kU-6IM-bSFp3IjD4oniP9hXK7Id_cykgnrop6g==]. Ensure your data is correctly formatted for the model [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEI40k-KKEZckGHxyNubfIsolqxboJcEBVFNhs1dpAaEpQ3OCfE3WxetAi57fkE8i4lCF85Uq5-Z76zu6LRatb2uEULsrONfhL45Z7_WsDb5YvEGXFYFO3XIylUd02BidJokldzgzmnKSa-5BVUY77P1xO5x4_VZD52]. Data issues are a common cause of problems [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEI40k-KKEZckGHxyNubfIsolqxboJcEBVFNhs1dpAaEpQ3OCfE3WxetAi57fkE8i4lCF85Uq5-Z76zu6LRatb2uEULsrONfhL45Z7_WsDb5YvEGXFYFO3XIylUd02BidJokldzgzmnKSa-5BVUY77P1xO5x4_VZD52].
2.  **Parameter Value Exceeds Maximum:** If the error message indicates a parameter value is too large, adjust it to fall within the allowed range [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFXiBJFyAK8csIanbE9Jcm6DxJgaAX183f_OrHenr310pAPpCo75Y8SDit_vC1C7C04B8Yc2jn9FC2TP2WXXJpNg0rTKUwX4aJdtfFjeFzBP_5DWqipBJNMDqlUAaHBPHx9p3unslCJG9m1kU-6IM-bSFp3IjD4oniP9hXK7Id_cykgnrop6g==]. For example, a `top_p` parameter might have received a value of 100 when it should be between 0 and 1 [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFXiBJFyAK8csIanbE9Jcm6DxJgaAX183f_OrHenr310pAPpCo75Y8SDit_vC1C7C04B8Yc2jn9FC2TP2WXXJpNg0rTKUwX4aJdtfFjeFzBP_5DWqipBJNMDqlUAaHBPHx9p3unslCJG9m1kU-6IM-bSFp3IjD4oniP9hXK7Id_cykgnrop6g==].
3.  **Missing or Invalid API Key:** Make sure you're including a valid API key/token in the request [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFXiBJFyAK8csIanbE9Jcm6DxJgaAX183f_OrHenr310pAPpCo75Y8SDit_vC1C7C04B8Yc2jn9FC2TP2WXXJpNg0rTKUwX4aJdtfFjeFzBP_5DWqipBJNMDqlUAaHBPHx9p3unslCJG9m1kU-6IM-bSFp3IjD4oniP9hXK7Id_cykgnrop6g==]. Generate and use a valid API key from the SambaNova Cloud portal [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFXiBJFyAK8csIanbE9Jcm6DxJgaAX183f_OrHenr310pAPpCo75Y8SDit_vC1C7C04B8Yc2jn9FC2TP2WXXJpNg0rTKUwX4aJdtfFjeFzBP_5DWqipBJNMDqlUAaHBPHx9p3unslCJG9m1kU-6IM-bSFp3IjD4oniP9hXK7Id_cykgnrop6g==].
4.  **Model Not Found:** Verify the model ID and ensure it's available in your subscription [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFXiBJFyAK8csIanbE9Jcm6DxJgaAX183f_OrHenr310pAPpCo75Y8SDit_vC1C7C04B8Yc2jn9FC2TP2WXXJpNg0rTKUwX4aJdtfFjeFzBP_5DWqipBJNMDqlUAaHBPHx9p3unslCJG9m1kU-6IM-bSFp3IjD4oniP9hXK7Id_cykgnrop6g==]. Check for case sensitivity issues in the model name [github](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHMxC0WDOZ1HAB7ciXpuV1ye7H4WJFqNRsMWh5A_RHRPzJFzPijhjvcEGHm-wGrnLgGp8LIuxrW7Q1T7mXBSao53RWd2DCnA35sKrcyGHXcVsZfCExjnt3EzVye4dsCTjIyTNnzkYZPyHPnqlYTgpVc].
5.  **Request Timeout:** If the server terminated the request due to excessive processing time, retry with an optimized payload [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFXiBJFyAK8csIanbE9Jcm6DxJgaAX183f_OrHenr310pAPpCo75Y8SDit_vC1C7C04B8Yc2jn9FC2TP2WXXJpNg0rTKUwX4aJdtfFjeFzBP_5DWqipBJNMDqlUAaHBPHx9p3unslCJG9m1kU-6IM-bSFp3IjD4oniP9hXK7Id_cykgnrop6g==].
6.  **Rate Limiting/Queue Full:** A 429 error (Too Many Requests) means you've exceeded your rate limit or too many requests are in flight [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFXiBJFyAK8csIanbE9Jcm6DxJgaAX183f_OrHenr310pAPpCo75Y8SDit_vC1C7C04B8Yc2jn9FC2TP2WXXJpNg0rTKUwX4aJdtfFjeFzBP_5DWqipBJNMDqlUAaHBPHx9p3unslCJG9m1kU-6IM-bSFp3IjD4oniP9hXK7Id_cykgnrop6g==]. Implement rate limiting, upgrade your tier, retry after a delay, or reduce concurrency [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFXiBJFyAK8csIanbE9Jcm6DxJgaAX183f_OrHenr310pAPpCo75Y8SDit_vC1C7C04B8Yc2jn9FC2TP2WXXJpNg0rTKUwX4aJdtfFjeFzBP_5DWqipBJNMDqlUAaHBPHx9p3unslCJG9m1kU-6IM-bSFp3IjD4oniP9hXK7Id_cykgnrop6g==].
7.  **Deprecated Model:** Use a currently supported model if the requested model is no longer available [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFXiBJFyAK8csIanbE9Jcm6DxJgaAX183f_OrHenr310pAPpCo75Y8SDit_vC1C7C04B8Yc2jn9FC2TP2WXXJpNg0rTKUwX4aJdtfFjeFzBP_5DWqipBJNMDqlUAaHBPHx9p3unslCJG9m1kU-6IM-bSFp3IjD4oniP9hXK7Id_cykgnrop6g==].
8.  **Context Length Exceeded:** Reduce the prompt and response length if the input/output tokens exceed the model context limits [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFXiBJFyAK8csIanbE9Jcm6DxJgaAX183f_OrHenr310pAPpCo75Y8SDit_vC1C7C04B8Yc2jn9FC2TP2WXXJpNg0rTKUwX4aJdtfFjeFzBP_5DWqipBJNMDqlUAaHBPHx9p3unslCJG9m1kU-6IM-bSFp3IjD4oniP9hXK7Id_cykgnrop6g==].
9.  **Parameter Type Mismatch:** Ensure the parameter types match what's expected (e.g., int vs. float) [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFXiBJFyAK8csIanbE9Jcm6DxJgaAX183f_OrHenr310pAPpCo75Y8SDit_vC1C7C04B8Yc2jn9FC2TP2WXXJpNg0rTKUwX4aJdtfFjeFzBP_5DWqipBJNMDqlUAaHBPHx9p3unslCJG9m1kU-6IM-bSFp3IjD4oniP9hXK7Id_cykgnrop6g==].

Here are some general troubleshooting steps:

*   **Check the URL:** Ensure the URL you are using is correct [quora](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG6Lt6fxkcfIJiOzi0SNEmfLpp5eyE9oH2JvH6NkMN77usUKPOwcua41eXWwePsH-Dy4YuE_aERV4L0pMTlhc6zghjNjqjdVx89H2Ukd3Lwvqh4aygCOrz1DxzFM8sPfUoWoBdd6QLBDJ5cNfYL9j4Wx19Ns9LYvrDoCBQS7Tl_yoblNyMR3Os=].
*   **Clear Browser Cache and Cookies:** Clear your browser's cache and cookies, especially if you're getting the error with a Google service [quora](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG6Lt6fxkcfIJiOzi0SNEmfLpp5eyE9oH2JvH6NkMN77usUKPOwcua41eXWwePsH-Dy4YuE_aERV4L0pMTlhc6zghjNjqjdVx89H2Ukd3Lwvqh4aygCOrz1DxzFM8sPfUoWoBdd6QLBDJ5cNfYL9j4Wx19Ns9LYvrDoCBQS7Tl_yoblNyMR3Os=].
*   **Check System Status:** If others are running models, the system might be overloaded [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF2G5Z_yRGGytgJmEAWXPbkzS4Knv7ts7eSxKgNY4NeKx9xV6Z3y-KBx9NgEzzXECRxNVeMaAjMpRxfCrkkp8xI1bIfcw4T59_e5hGWDj_0rW5BUGb01p_e71iBP5S-DN5kCxfOC1gndIIvtaPKmITm_LolMYRf-zQd2uwSuf-h6g==]. Wait and try again, and ask your system administrator to check the system's health with `sntilestat` [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF2G5Z_yRGGytgJmEAWXPbkzS4Knv7ts7eSxKgNY4NeKx9xV6Z3y-KBx9NgEzzXECRxNVeMaAjMpRxfCrkkp8xI1bIfcw4T59_e5hGWDj_0rW5BUGb01p_e71iBP5S-DN5kCxfOC1gndIIvtaPKmITm_LolMYRf-zQd2uwSuf-h6g==].
*   **Contact Support:** If the problem persists, contact SambaNova support [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFXiBJFyAK8csIanbE9Jcm6DxJgaAX183f_OrHenr310pAPpCo75Y8SDit_vC1C7C04B8Yc2jn9FC2TP2WXXJpNg0rTKUwX4aJdtfFjeFzBP_5DWqipBJNMDqlUAaHBPHx9p3unslCJG9m1kU-6IM-bSFp3IjD4oniP9hXK7Id_cykgnrop6g==) [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF2G5Z_yRGGytgJmEAWXPbkzS4Knv7ts7eSxKgNY4NeKx9xV6Z3y-KBx9NgEzzXECRxNVeMaAjMpRxfCrkkp8xI1bIfcw4T59_e5hGWDj_0rW5BUGb01p_e71iBP5S-DN5kCxfOC1gndIIvtaPKmITm_LolMYRf-zQd2uwSuf-h6g==].

SambaNova tools and best practices include:

*   **SambaNova Fault Management (snfadm):** Use `snfadm` at `/opt/sambaflow/bin/snfadm` for basic checks [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEI40k-KKEZckGHxyNubfIsolqxboJcEBVFNhs1dpAaEpQ3OCfE3WxetAi57fkE8i4lCF85Uq5-Z76zu6LRatb2uEULsrONfhL45Z7_WsDb5YvEGXFYFO3XIylUd02BidJokldzgzmnKSa-5BVUY77P1xO5x4_VZD52]. For example:
    *   `snfadm -l inventory | less`
    *   `snfadm -l fault`
    *   `snfadm -l error`
*   **Check SambaNova Daemon Status:** Run `systemctl status snd` to check the SambaNova daemon status if you see unexpected errors [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEI40k-KKEZckGHxyNubfIsolqxboJcEBVFNhs1dpAaEpQ3OCfE3WxetAi57fkE8i4lCF85Uq5-Z76zu6LRatb2uEULsrONfhL45Z7_WsDb5YvEGXFYFO3XIylUd02BidJokldzgzmnKSa-5BVUY77P1xO5x4_VZD52].
*   **Compilation:** Ensure that the model compile and run phases use the same definition of the model [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEI40k-KKEZckGHxyNubfIsolqxboJcEBVFNhs1dpAaEpQ3OCfE3WxetAi57fkE8i4lCF85Uq5-Z76zu6LRatb2uEULsrONfhL45Z7_WsDb5YvEGXFYFO3XIylUd02BidJokldzgzmnKSa-5BVUY77P1xO5x4_VZD52].

*   **BF16 Format:** Use BF16 in your code where possible, for checkpoints, and for preprocessed datasets [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEI40k-KKEZckGHxyNubfIsolqxboJcEBVFNhs1dpAaEpQ3OCfE3WxetAi57fkE8i4lCF85Uq5-Z76zu6LRatb2uEULsrONfhL45Z7_WsDb5YvEGXFYFO3XIylUd02BidJokldzgzmnKSa-5BVUY77P1xO5x4_VZD52].

A "400 Bad Request" error with SambaNova indicates that the server couldn't process the request due to invalid syntax or input values [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). Here's a breakdown of troubleshooting steps based on the search results:

**1. Understanding the Error**

*   A 400 error generally means the client (your application or browser) sent a request that the server couldn't understand [quora](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1). This could be due to a malformed request, invalid arguments, or other client-side issues [quora](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1).
*   SambaNova Cloud API uses standard HTTP response status codes to indicate the success or failure of API requests [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2) [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). When a request fails, the API responds with a JSON object containing details about the error, including an error code, the parameter causing the error (if applicable), and a helpful error message [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2) [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).

**2. Common Causes and Solutions**

*   **Invalid Syntax or Input Values**: Review the API request syntax and parameters [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). Ensure that the data is properly formatted for the model you're working with [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3). Data issues are a common cause of problems [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3).
*   **Parameter Value Exceeds Maximum**: The error message might indicate that a parameter value exceeded the allowed maximum [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). Adjust the value to fall within the allowed range [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). For example, a `top_p` parameter might have received a value of 100 when it should be between 0 and 1 [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).
*   **Missing or Invalid API Key**: Ensure a valid API key/token is included in the request [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). Generate and use a valid API key from the SambaNova Cloud portal [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).
*   **Model Not Found**: If you encounter a "Model not found" error, verify the model ID and ensure it's available in your subscription [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). Also, check for potential case sensitivity issues in the model name [github](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4).
*   **Request Timeout**: The server might have terminated the request due to excessive processing time [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). Retry the request with an optimized payload [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).
*   **Rate Limiting**: If you receive a 429 error (Too Many Requests), you've exceeded the rate limit for your subscription tier [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). Implement rate limiting or upgrade your tier [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).
*   **Queue Full**: A 429 error can also indicate that too many requests are currently in flight [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). Retry after a short delay or reduce concurrency [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).
*   **Deprecated Model**: The requested model might no longer be available [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). Use a currently supported model [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).
*   **Context Length Exceeded**: If the input/output tokens exceed the model context limits, reduce the prompt and response length [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).
*   **Parameter Type Mismatch**: Check the expected parameter types and correct the input if there's a mismatch (e.g., expected int but got float) [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).

**3. General Troubleshooting Steps**

*   **Check the URL**: Ensure the URL you are using is correct [quora](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1).
*   **Clear Browser Cache and Cookies**: Clear your browser's cache and cookies, especially if you're getting the error with a Google service [quora](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1).
*   **Check System Status**: If you know that others are also running models on the system, the problem might be that their models are using too many resources [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5). Wait and try again later [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5). Ask your system administrator to check if the system is healthy and to run `sntilestat` to see the status of the hardware [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5).
*   **Contact Support**: If the problem persists, contact SambaNova support [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5).

**4. Tools and Best Practices**

*   **SambaNova Fault Management (snfadm)**: Use `snfadm` at `/opt/sambaflow/bin/snfadm` for basic checks [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3). For example:
    *   `snfadm -l inventory | less`
    *   `snfadm -l fault`
    *   `snfadm -l error`
*   **Check SambaNova Daemon Status**: Run `systemctl status snd` to check the SambaNova daemon status if you see unexpected errors [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3).
*   **Compilation**: Ensure that the model compile and run phases use the same definition of the model [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3). Otherwise, you'll see missing or mismatched tensor errors when you run the model [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3).
*   **Data Preparation**: Ensure that data is properly formatted for the model you're working with [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3).
*   **BF16 Format**: Use BF16 in your code where possible, for checkpoints, and for preprocessed datasets [sambanova](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3).

By systematically checking these potential issues and utilizing the provided tools, you should be able to diagnose and resolve the SambaNova error 400.
